"{\"uid\": \"news.cgtn.com-news-2024-08-13-Five-time-Olympic-medalist-Tom-Daley-announces-retirement-from-diving-1w1yI2ZTvAQ-p.html\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"Our Privacy Statement & Cookie Policy  By continuing to browse our site you agree to our use of cookies, revised Privacy Policy and Terms of Use.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 145, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"You can change your cookie settings through your browser.\", \"from\": 146, \"to\": 203, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Sports Scene  Copied  Team GB diverTom Daley comes back to London after pariticipating in the 2024 Olympic Games in Paris, France, August 12, 2024.\", \"from\": 205, \"to\": 352, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 264, \"end\": 270, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.999994807994717, \"rank\": 2.7060781411113395e-06, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}, {\"begin\": 321, \"end\": 326, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999896142526, \"rank\": 1.0385645591217885e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 328, \"end\": 334, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.6544389660622902, \"rank\": 0.2745836359933806, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"/CFP  Five-time Olympic medalist Tom Daley announced his retirement from diving on Monday.\", \"from\": 353, \"to\": 443, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 386, \"end\": 395, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Daley\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1012300565148833e-48, \"text\": \"Tom Daley\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Daley\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tom_Daley\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Daley told British Vogue magazine he had decided to call time on his career.\", \"from\": 445, \"to\": 521, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 456, \"end\": 469, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Vogue\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 7.27585098069068e-22, \"text\": \"British Vogue\", \"types\": [\"Q41298\", \"Q386724\", \"Q234460\", \"Q1092563\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Vogue\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Vogue\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The 30-year-old British diver competed at five Games, making his debut at Beijing 2008 and winning gold and bronze in Tokyo, silver in Paris and bronzes at London 2012 and Rio 2016.\", \"from\": 523, \"to\": 704, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 539, \"end\": 546, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\", \"score\": 0.9602036462398253, \"rank\": 0.04113123913830464, \"text\": \"British\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/British_Boxing_Board_of_Control\"}, {\"begin\": 641, \"end\": 646, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9702658470334056, \"rank\": 0.03064503810410011, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 658, \"end\": 663, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999896142526, \"rank\": 1.0385645591217885e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 679, \"end\": 690, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999869116892, \"rank\": 1.3084514527767353e-08, \"text\": \"London 2012\", \"types\": [\"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/2012_Summer_Olympics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Daley, who claimed his fifth Olympic medal in the 10m synchronized event in Paris last month, said in the interview: \\\"It feels very, very surreal.\", \"from\": 706, \"to\": 852, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 782, \"end\": 787, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999896142526, \"rank\": 1.0385645591217885e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I felt so incredibly nervous going into this, knowing it was my last Olympics.\\\"\", \"from\": 853, \"to\": 932, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There was a lot of pressure and expectations.\", \"from\": 934, \"to\": 980, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I was eager for it to be done,\\\" he added.\", \"from\": 981, \"to\": 1022, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"But when I walked out and saw my husband (Lance) and kids (Robbie and Phoenix) and my friends and family in the audience, I was like, you know what?\", \"from\": 1023, \"to\": 1172, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1083, \"end\": 1089, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_Donnachaidh\", \"score\": 0.9861985303559909, \"rank\": 0.009598913245941884, \"text\": \"Robbie\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_Donnachaidh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_Donnachaidh\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This is exactly why I did this.\", \"from\": 1173, \"to\": 1204, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"...\", \"from\": 1205, \"to\": 1208, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It was emotional at the end, up there on the platform, knowing it was going to be my last competitive dive.\", \"from\": 1209, \"to\": 1316, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But I have to make the decision at some point, and it feels like the right time.\", \"from\": 1317, \"to\": 1397, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It's the right time to call it a day.\\u00e2\\u0080\\u009d  Daley's gold came in the 10m synchronized event in Tokyo in 2021 alongside Matty Lee.\", \"from\": 1398, \"to\": 1525, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1491, \"end\": 1496, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"score\": 0.9702658470334056, \"rank\": 0.03064503810410011, \"text\": \"Tokyo\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tokyo\"}, {\"begin\": 1515, \"end\": 1524, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matty_Lee\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Matty Lee\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matty_Lee\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matty_Lee\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"He was back to defend his title in Paris after being convinced by his son Robbie to return to the sport.\", \"from\": 1526, \"to\": 1630, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1561, \"end\": 1566, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999896142526, \"rank\": 1.0385645591217885e-08, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1600, \"end\": 1606, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_Donnachaidh\", \"score\": 0.9861985303559909, \"rank\": 0.009598913245941884, \"text\": \"Robbie\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_Donnachaidh\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Clan_Donnachaidh\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Daley won silver in the French capital alongside Noah Williams.\", \"from\": 1632, \"to\": 1695, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1656, \"end\": 1662, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/French_language\", \"score\": 0.7305377187155118, \"rank\": 0.35957113640448524, \"text\": \"French\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/res